so how can 2 billion won be a big deal to him when he's part of Century Group?

113
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:10,600
That's when you go in.

114
00:10:10,660 --> 00:10:14,060
He's trying to buy a woman's heart with money now? That's cheap.

115
00:10:14,060 --> 00:10:15,350
What?

116
00:10:15,350 --> 00:10:19,400
So, if that happens, is she going to change her mind?

117
00:10:19,400 --> 00:10:24,000
You said she was from the Cheongsong family, but she was this kind of easy woman? Being from a prestigious family is nothing special!

118
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:26,850
Tell them to be happy. I won't ...

119
00:10:26,850 --> 00:10:29,690
I won't have to do anything and I'll get my 2 billion won!

120
00:10:29,690 --> 00:10:31,330
Then that's just great!

121
00:10:31,330 --> 00:10:33,490
Why is it so hot? Damn it!

122
00:10:33,490 --> 00:10:37,310
Hey, drive carefully. I'm getting carsick!

123
00:10:40,310 --> 00:10:42,640
What's wrong with this?

124
00:10:56,890 --> 00:11:00,210
[Dondon]

125
00:11:12,710 --> 00:11:17,520
Oh, you're back? Did they say they'll give you the money? It's still Cheongsong, so they won't go bankrupt right away. Right?

126
00:11:18,500 --> 00:11:21,700
- What are you doing in my office?
- What?

127
00:11:25,060 --> 00:11:30,550
Well, I was wondering what happened to you because you went to the art museum.

128
00:11:31,240 --> 00:11:34,770
But you sound a bit weird.

129
00:11:34,770 --> 00:11:37,370
Why are you talking to me as if I'm a stranger?

130
00:11:37,370 --> 00:11:41,260
Do I need permission to visit my brother's office?

131
00:11:44,710 --> 00:11:49,020
So what happened? Do they have any money for us?

132
00:11:49,800 --> 00:11:52,230
If they say they don't have it, are we not going to get paid back?

133
00:11:52,230 --> 00:11:56,040
Don't worry. I'll get it no matter what.

134
00:11:58,120 --> 00:12:01,730
Right. You're not the type who would be easily scammed.

135
00:12:06,070 --> 00:12:10,260
But... let's make one thing clear.

136
00:12:10,260 --> 00:12:13,250
The only thing I did was to introduce you to Cheongsong.

137
00:12:13,300 --> 00:12:17,300
It was you who made the final decision to lend the money.

138
00:12:17,500 --> 00:12:19,100
Right?

139
00:12:22,100 --> 00:12:23,300
What did you say?

140
00:12:24,570 --> 00:12:29,290
Well, that's the truth. It's best to make that clear.

141
00:12:29,900 --> 00:12:31,660
Then I'll let you get back to work.

142
00:12:31,660 --> 00:12:33,270
- Brother.
- Yes?

143
00:12:36,890 --> 00:12:42,230
You know, the director of Cheongsong Art Museum. The man who passed away.

144
00:12:42,230 --> 00:12:43,760
What about him?

145
00:12:43,760 --> 00:12:48,360
How did he die? Did he have any illnesses?

146
00:12:49,090 --> 00:12:51,610
How would I know that?

147
00:12:51,610 --> 00:12:56,750
Well, you were the one who made the introduction, and you also met him the day before he passed away.

148
00:12:56,750 --> 00:12:59,900
Why would I meet with him?

149
00:12:59,900 --> 00:13:05,440
Wasn't that the day I left on the business trip to the Netherlands? You were going to meet him on my behalf.

150
00:13:08,340 --> 00:13:11,570
Oh, that. Father found out about the loan

151
00:13:11,570 --> 00:13:14,430
so I wasn't able to go because he was going crazy about it.

152
00:13:14,430 --> 00:13:18,380
How could I have gone when he was like that? I didn't want to take the blame.

153
00:13:19,020 --> 00:13:20,690
That's true.

154
00:13:25,620 --> 00:13:27,640
Get to your work.

155
00:13:37,130 --> 00:13:41,120
[Director Office]

156
00:13:41,120 --> 00:13:44,490
- I need you to give back the investment money.
- What?

157
00:13:47,370 --> 00:13:50,400
How dare you come here?

158
