00:21:04,780 --> 00:21:08,280
- Was it you?
- No.

249
00:21:08,280 --> 00:21:11,120
- You!
- N-No.

250
00:21:11,120 --> 00:21:14,610
Then, was it you?

251
00:21:14,610 --> 00:21:16,490
It wasn't me.

252
00:21:16,490 --> 00:21:21,370
Then... What do you mean no?! It was you!

253
00:21:21,370 --> 00:21:25,200
- How dare you try to pull one on me again?
- Ma'am, she's not trying to pull one on you.

254
00:21:25,200 --> 00:21:28,480
- First, let's calm down, ma'am.
- Don't tell me to calm down.

255
00:21:28,480 --> 00:21:30,960
Hey, what did you tell me last time?

256
00:21:30,960 --> 00:21:35,020
You said the old geezer who painted that painting was about to die. That the painting would be worth double as soon as he died.

257
00:21:35,020 --> 00:21:38,530
You said I could even make four times the money!

258
00:21:38,530 --> 00:21:40,490
Did I?

259
00:21:40,490 --> 00:21:43,320
Hey. That old man got remarried

260
00:21:43,320 --> 00:21:45,610
to a young girl in her twenties.

261
00:21:45,610 --> 00:21:48,530
He even had kids at that age. Twins!

262
00:21:48,530 --> 00:21:50,800
Oh, I see! Kids at that age. Twins.

263
00:21:50,800 --> 00:21:53,640
Ma'am, about the art,

264
00:21:53,640 --> 00:21:58,250
unlike from stocks or real estate, you have to look far out in the long run.

265
00:21:58,250 --> 00:22:02,710
That old man's painting was sold at half the price at the auction a couple of days ago!

266
00:22:02,710 --> 00:22:04,510
What are you going to do about my money now?

267
00:22:04,510 --> 00:22:08,650
What are you going to do about my money?

268
00:22:08,650 --> 00:22:12,040
You bitch!

269
00:22:12,040 --> 00:22:16,670
Oh, no!

270
00:22:16,670 --> 00:22:20,830
Hey! Hey!

271
00:22:20,830 --> 00:22:25,780
There are still ignorant people like that? And you just stood there?

272
00:22:25,780 --> 00:22:29,940
What was I supposed to do? She's a VIP customer.

273
00:22:29,940 --> 00:22:34,600
They're being ruder because you're submissive to them just because they're the customer!

274
00:22:34,600 --> 00:22:39,500
An eye for an eye! Ear for an ear! You have to be more firm!

275
00:22:41,080 --> 00:22:46,060
Moo Hak, what do you mean ear? It's a nose.

276
00:22:46,120 --> 00:22:48,140
An eye for an eye, a nose for a nose.

277
00:22:48,140 --> 00:22:50,380
[An eye for an eye, a tooth for a tooth.]

278
00:22:50,380 --> 00:22:53,990
- What the?
- Oh my god.

279
00:22:53,990 --> 00:22:56,300
What does it matter as long as you understand?

280
00:22:56,300 --> 00:23:00,330
This is the line between us that we can't cross.

281
00:23:00,330 --> 00:23:03,840
You're way too ignorant.

282
00:23:10,100 --> 00:23:15,690
Wow... that lady was only a grime in the bucket.
[A drop in the bucket]
(T/N: nothing in comparison to)

283
00:23:15,690 --> 00:23:20,320
- What is it?
- Look at this. Aren't they the worst?
[A drop (not a grime) in the bucket]

284
00:23:20,320 --> 00:23:24,200
Do they have nowhere better to make a scene? How could they do this at an art museum?

285
00:23:24,200 --> 00:23:26,600
This is what's really ignorant.

286
00:23:26,600 --> 00:23:29,680
So what if you don't know English and don't understand a few idioms well?

287
00:23:29,680 --> 00:23:34,550
At least you wouldn't do bullish things like this in front of works of art.

288
00:23:34,550 --> 00:23:39,590
I mean, I'm sure there was some kind of reason.

289
00:23:39,590 --> 00:23:42,130
Reason my foot.

290
00:23:43,890 --> 00:23:45,890
Wait.

291
00:23:48,280 --> 00:23:51,120
I've seen this silhouette before somewhere.

292
00:23:56,610 --> 00:23:59,180
Here, eat this.

293
00:23:59,180 --> 00:24:04,480
Auntie, I'd like to add another serving of sundae! With extra lung and liver.
(T/N: sundae - sausage made of beef and bean curd stuffed in pig intestine)

294
00:24:05,910 --> 00:24:09,660
Anyway, it's over for Cheongsong.

295
00:24:09,660 --> 00:24:11,670
What do you mean it's over?

296
00:24:11,670 --> 00:24:14,900
Who would want to see art at an art museum with gangsters?

297
00:24:14,900 --> 00:24:17,170
What artist would want to exhibit their art there?

298
00:24:17,170 --> 00:24:20,780
An art museum with no art and no visitors has no choice but to close.

299
00:24:20,780 --> 00:24:25,630
I'm sure the rumors have spread already.

300
00:24:30,190 --> 00:24:33,940
There's still so much time until the settlement day. Why are you so worried?

301
00:24:33,940 --> 00:24:37,790
How many years of trust do we share, President Jeong?

302
00:24:37,790 --> 00:24:40,490
There's no problem with Cheongsong.

303
00:24:40,490 --> 00:24:45,010
It's true! Oh, one minute, President.

304
00:24:45,010 --> 00:24:49,410
You don't have to worry about that. Our new director is here—

305
00:24:49,410 --> 00:24:54,330
Excuse me? Oh, of course. I will visit with our new director soon.

306
00:24:54,330 --> 00:24:56,790
- Yes, goodbye.
- Oh, yes.

307
00:24:56,790 --> 00:24:59,580
One moment, please.

308
00:24:59,580 --> 00:25:05,050
Hello? Oh, yes. The exhibition is in progress without any problems.

309
00:25:05,050 --> 00:25:07,100
The loan money?

310
00:25:07,100 --> 00:25:10,940
I'm not too sure about that— One moment, please.

311
00:25:12,700 --> 00:25:16,470
- Hello, the call was transferred to me.
- It was a small issue due to a misunderstanding.

312
00:25:16,470 --> 00:25:19,120
It will be resolved soon.

313
00:25:19,120 --> 00:25:23,420
I was going to arrange a meeting to greet the members...

314
00:25:25,870 --> 00:25:28,550
Daerim Bank.

315
00:25:30,510 --> 00:25:34,220
Yes, I'll get back to you after setting the date, then.

316
00:25:35,660 --> 00:25:37,930
Yes, this is Kim Dali.

317
00:25:38,860 --> 00:25:43,450
No, it was just a small issue because of a misunderstanding. It will be resolved soon.

318
00:25:43,450 --> 00:25:48,000
If you have a little patience, we'll resolve it without issue. Yes.

319
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:50,640
Yes, don't worry. Of course.

320
00:25:52,170 --> 00:25:56,190
Hi, Curator Choi! Oh, you saw it too?

321
00:25:56,190 --> 00:26:00,410
No, it's not like that.

322
00:26:22,110 --> 00:26:25,530
You all did really great today. Please, get home safe.

323
00:26:25,530 --> 00:26:28,120
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

324
00:26:28,120 --> 00:26:32,140
- Take care.
- Take care.

325
00:26:34,630 --> 00:26:40,730
They're really going at her from her day one.

326
00:26:40,730 --> 00:26:43,350
She should be able to handle at least that much.

327
00:26:44,980 --> 00:26:47,180
What's with her...?

328
00:26:48,950 --> 00:26:53,540
- I don't know.
- Oh, the day is so long.

329
00:26:59,050 --> 00:27:02,690
You must have gotten the money, seeing as you're going home on time.

330
00:27:23,110 --> 00:27:25,790
Are you all right?

331
00:27:28,610 --> 00:27:32,050
Mr. Jin. Mr. Jin.

332
00:27:32,050 --> 00:27:36,960
Ah, yes, yes.

333
00:27:44,290 --> 00:27:47,690
Why did you come back here again?

334
00:27:47,690 --> 00:27:51,330
I mean, I just heard it was a mess.

335
00:27:51,330 --> 00:27:55,020
Did you come because you were worried about me?

336
00:27:55,020 --> 00:28:00,760
What do you mean "worry"? I came to make sure you weren't going to flee in the night with my money.

337
00:28:00,760 --> 00:28:05,440
Oh, right. You said we were nothing more or less than a debtor and creditor.

338
00:28:05,440 --> 00:28:08,490
You told me not to act close.

339
00:28:08,490 --> 00:28:11,130
You know well.

340
00:28:12,990 --> 00:28:15,790
Now what? What's the matter?

341
00:28:15,790 --> 00:28:23,680
Why...?

342
00:28:23,680 --> 00:28:27,150
Why the hell do you wear those?

343
00:28:27,150 --> 00:28:30,810
Are you trying to collect accident insurance money?

344
00:28:30,810 --> 00:28:36,060
I don't even think these are pretty. They're just scary.

345
00:28:36,060 --> 00:28:42,160
My luggage hasn't arrived from the Netherlands yet. These are the only shoes I have.

346
00:28:46,540 --> 00:28:51,530
Don't worry too much.

347
00:28:53,090 --> 00:28:57,830
What do you mean "worry"? Who's worrying? Why do you keep saying that?

348
00:28:57,830 --> 00:29:00,910
Why would I worry about you? Whether the art museum's a mess,

349
00:29:00,910 --> 00:29:04,800
- or you break your leg, why would it matter to me?
- No, I mean

350
00:29:04,800 --> 00:29:08,370
I won't escape in the night, so you don't have to worry.

351
00:29:10,450 --> 00:29:15,950
♫ Time will be on your side, and you'll be ♫

352
00:29:15,950 --> 00:29:18,290
Just stay there for a moment.

353
00:29:21,250 --> 00:29:25,250
♫ One day it'll be ♫

354
00:29:30,520 --> 00:29:33,200
Wear these for now.

355
00:29:33,200 --> 00:29:36,050
No, it's okay. I can just do this.

356
00:29:37,020 --> 00:29:41,750
We're just debtor and creditor. I shouldn't do anything to owe you.

357
00:29:42,860 --> 00:29:45,720
I thought you said that saying "thank you" was enough.

358
00:29:48,120 --> 00:29:49,920
You said that in the Netherlands.

359
00:29:49,920 --> 00:29:54,580
That when someone does you a favor, all you have to say is "thank you."

360
00:30:16,590 --> 00:30:19,730
You really don't have to do this.

361
00:30:21,850 --> 00:30:25,450
Did you hear the news about your father on that day?

362
00:30:25,530 --> 00:30:27,890
That day?

363
00:30:27,890 --> 00:30:31,400
You know, the day we said goodbye at the hotel.

364
00:30:33,490 --> 00:30:36,470
I guess so.

365
00:30:36,470 --> 00:30:40,730
Everything happened so quickly,

366
00:30:40,730 --> 00:30:44,640
so I can't even tell what's forward or backward.

367
00:30:44,640 --> 00:30:50,560
How I came to Korea? How did the funeral take place?

368
00:30:53,920 --> 00:30:57,750
Oh right! We had said we'd meet at the art museum.

369
00:31:03,210 --> 00:31:05,290
Did you wait long for me?

370
00:31:05,290 --> 00:31:08,560
No, why would I wait for you?

371
00:31:08,560 --> 00:31:11,750
I told you that my schedule was very busy that day.

372
00:31:11,750 --> 00:31:15,750
I called to tell you I couldn't make time, but you didn't pick up.

373
00:31:15,750 --> 00:31:19,250
I just thought "She must be busy" and moved on.

374
00:31:19,250 --> 00:31:21,720
Very cool.

375
00:31:21,720 --> 00:31:25,620
Did you know my phone number?

376
00:31:30,830 --> 00:31:33,530
I called the library. No, I—

377
00:31:33,530 --> 00:31:39,830
called the museum. I mean, I called the art gallery.

378
00:31:39,830 --> 00:31:43,420
The art gallery gave you my personal phone number?

379
00:31:43,420 --> 00:31:47,360
I told them I was your childhood friend and they gave it to me.

380
00:31:47,360 --> 00:31:49,760
Oh, I see.

381
00:31:49,760 --> 00:31:53,800
I'm a businessman, you think I wouldn't be able to do that much?

382
00:31:56,130 --> 00:31:58,050
- But–
- It's true!

383
00:31:58,050 --> 00:32:02,310
Do you think I would have hired a private investigator or something just to get your phone number?

384
00:32:03,520 --> 00:32:07,930
It's not that. We're here.

385
00:32:07,930 --> 00:32:11,820
You can drop me off over there. Thank you.

386
00:32:13,230 --> 00:32:14,650
Okay.

387
00:32:26,780 --> 00:32:30,970
Is it over there...?

388
00:32:39,550 --> 00:32:42,090
Are you following me right now?

389
00:32:43,180 --> 00:32:48,670
What do you mean? Since I'm at the department store, I am going to see if there is anything new.

390
00:32:48,670 --> 00:32:51,340
I come here often. I'm diamond-level.

391
00:32:51,340 --> 00:32:53,960
I even use the exclusive lounge!

392
00:32:53,960 --> 00:32:55,530
I see.

393
00:33:12,690 --> 00:33:15,540
♫ I keep getting excited ♫

394
00:33:15,540 --> 00:33:19,240
♫ I love you, love you, love you, I’m only thinking about you again ♫

395
00:33:19,240 --> 00:33:20,700
Was it on the third floor?

396
00:33:20,700 --> 00:33:23,560
♫ I keep getting nervous ♫

397
00:33:23,560 --> 00:33:28,230
♫ I like you, like you, like you. I wasn't like this before ♫

398
00:33:28,230 --> 00:33:36,250
♫ I can see my reflection from your eyes ♫

399
00:33:36,250 --> 00:33:44,250
♫ It shines like the moon that rises high in the night sky, yeah ♫

400
00:33:44,250 --> 00:33:48,180
I told you I wouldn't try to escape.

401
00:33:48,180 --> 00:33:52,190
No, I...

402
00:33:53,720 --> 00:33:58,690
I was going to get my shoes. They're very special to me.

403
00:34:03,650 --> 00:34:08,800
Okay, you can give them to me later. You must return them, okay?

404
00:34:14,750 --> 00:34:17,180
What? What's the matter?

405
00:34:17,180 --> 00:34:19,810
What? What? What is it?

406
00:34:19,810 --> 00:34:23,950
What? What are you doing? What?

407
00:34:23,950 --> 00:34:25,760
What are you— What the—

408
00:34:25,760 --> 00:34:28,660
What are you—?

409
00:34:47,510 --> 00:34:50,870
I'm sorry. You must be flustered.

410
00:34:53,620 --> 00:34:56,660
You're not going to ask why I did that?

411
00:34:56,660 --> 00:34:58,610
Am I supposed to be curious?

412
00:35:01,670 --> 00:35:03,950
You can go now.

413
00:35:04,840 --> 00:35:07,180
I feel like he's going to appear again. Is that okay?

414
00:35:07,180 --> 00:35:10,330
It seemed like you might run into him again, and it would be a problem.

415
00:35:10,330 --> 00:35:12,790
No, it's not like that.

416
00:35:16,150 --> 00:35:20,860
Let's go. Since I'm here, I will cover you until you are done.

417
00:35:20,860 --> 00:35:22,370
Here.

418
00:35:34,020 --> 00:35:36,780
- This place is really expensive.
- Pardon?

419
00:35:37,340 --> 00:35:39,570
I'm a regular here.

420
00:35:39,570 --> 00:35:41,550
Oh my, you're here!

421
00:35:41,550 --> 00:35:43,950
It hasn't even been a week, you don't have to overreact.

422
00:35:43,950 --> 00:35:45,280
How long has it been?

423
00:35:45,280 --> 00:35:46,410
Have you been well?

424
00:35:46,410 --> 00:35:49,350
Thanks to you. When did you come back from the Netherlands?

425
00:35:49,350 --> 00:35:51,740
Did you lose weight?

426
00:35:51,740 --> 00:35:53,680
I'm a regular here.

427
00:35:53,680 --> 00:35:57,420
One moment. Jeong Won, please escort our guest.

428
00:35:57,420 --> 00:36:00,860
Why don't we go over there? It's a little noisy here.

429
00:36:00,860 --> 00:36:03,040
Will you come this way?

430
00:36:03,040 --> 00:36:04,390
Jeong Won, bring us some tea, too.

431
00:36:04,390 --> 00:36:06,130
Yes, ma'am.

432
00:36:07,570 --> 00:36:10,880
I see the manager has changed.

433
00:36:12,200 --> 00:36:15,830
There's only one pair left in Korea.

434
00:36:17,700 --> 00:36:23,040
It's a shame, this avant-garde is just your style.

435
00:36:23,040 --> 00:36:25,430
What a load of crap.

436
00:36:25,430 --> 00:36:28,170
I'll be wearing it for work.

437
00:36:28,170 --> 00:36:29,890
I see.

438
00:36:33,360 --> 00:36:37,040
It says this card is suspended. Do you have another card?

439
00:36:37,040 --> 00:36:38,720
Oh, really?

440
00:36:40,710 --> 00:36:42,170
I'm sorry.

441
00:36:42,170 --> 00:36:44,140
Don't worry about it.

442
00:36:46,330 --> 00:36:49,620
This card is also suspended.

443
00:36:50,160 --> 00:36:53,000
That can't be...

444
00:36:53,000 --> 00:36:54,780
Use this card.

445
00:36:55,560 --> 00:36:56,790
Oppa.

446
00:36:56,790 --> 00:37:01,390
Grab a couple of outfits with matching shoes and a bag. You know her size, right?

447
00:37:01,390 --> 00:37:03,180
- Of course.
- No.

448
00:37:03,180 --> 00:37:06,750
Don't do that. What are you doing?

449
00:37:06,750 --> 00:37:11,090
You probably didn't even pack properly because you were in a rush to return home. Please, prepare it.

450
00:37:11,090 --> 00:37:12,980
- All right.
- No.

451
00:37:12,980 --> 00:37:15,030
Please don't.

452
00:37:15,030 --> 00:37:19,320
This is none of your business and we don't have that kind of relationship.

453
00:37:21,990 --> 00:37:28,390
Mr. Jin, what are you doing? We have to pay.

454
00:37:32,290 --> 00:37:36,000
Everyone is waiting.

455
00:37:45,670 --> 00:37:51,320
Right. I was distracted by the products. Let's pay.

456
00:37:51,320 --> 00:37:54,810
Please ring this up.

457
00:37:54,810 --> 00:37:56,360
Here you go.

458
00:37:58,750 --> 00:38:02,720
Oh, right. Hold on.

459
00:38:02,720 --> 00:38:05,230
Can we get the 5% off?

460
00:38:05,230 --> 00:38:07,640
We can't accept that here.

461
00:38:09,080 --> 00:38:12,220
Oh, it must be the store next door.

462
00:38:14,770 --> 00:38:16,370
What's the total?

463
00:38:16,370 --> 00:38:19,300
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

464
00:38:24,940 --> 00:38:26,920
Can we talk for a second?

465
00:38:26,920 --> 00:38:31,180
Not today, I have company. I'll go visit you next time.

466
00:38:31,180 --> 00:38:33,410
I have something to tell you, too.

467
00:38:38,100 --> 00:38:39,330
Let's go.

468
00:38:39,330 --> 00:38:41,150
Yes, let's.

469
00:39:05,490 --> 00:39:09,860
I'm sorry. I'm already a debtor to you. I'll be sure to pay you back for the card fee.

470
00:39:09,860 --> 00:39:14,820
No big deal. It's late. I can take you home—

471
00:39:16,220 --> 00:39:20,460
What? It's not like you weren't going to pay me back.

472
00:40:16,040 --> 00:40:20,270
Oppa! Oppa, Oppa!

473
00:40:21,350 --> 00:40:25,290
Why are you suddenly saying let's pretend none of this happened?

474
00:40:25,290 --> 00:40:30,430
One week. Our wedding is in one week. Why are you doing this?

475
00:40:32,000 --> 00:40:34,960
I'm sorry. It's all my fault. I'll fix everything.

476
00:40:34,960 --> 00:40:37,420
I'll do everything you want.

477
00:40:39,050 --> 00:40:42,110
Don't do this, Oppa.

478
00:40:42,110 --> 00:40:45,100
Oppa, look at me. I'm begging you.

479
00:40:45,100 --> 00:40:48,120
Please... Please...

480
00:40:58,210 --> 00:41:00,880
Can you really do what I want?

481
00:41:02,920 --> 00:41:04,780
I can.

482
00:41:05,940 --> 00:41:08,010
Anything?

483
00:41:08,010 --> 00:41:09,910
Anything.

484
00:41:14,630 --> 00:41:16,100
Then...

485
00:42:01,830 --> 00:42:05,390
This may be presumptuous, but can I say one thing?

486
00:42:06,080 --> 00:42:10,090
Taking care of the funeral may be all right because there is a connection between your families,

487
00:42:10,090 --> 00:42:14,990
but anything more than that can cause gossip. Especially today, there were a lot of people who were watching.

488
00:42:14,990 --> 00:42:17,800
If I was afraid of that, then I would have never started to begin with.

489
00:42:18,500 --> 00:42:21,040
I'm not the person I was five years ago.

490
00:42:21,920 --> 00:42:26,840
The reason I could endure after hurting Dali like that

491
00:42:26,840 --> 00:42:30,430
was because I believed I could get her back.

492
00:42:32,480 --> 00:42:35,030
I will get Dali back.

493
00:42:56,590 --> 00:42:58,980
Yes, Lawyer Cha.

494
00:43:01,690 --> 00:43:03,620
Is that so?

